{
  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_2' aria-label=\" Paritala Sudhakar versus State of Telangana pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('2','2025','2025_6_180_192','2025INSC655'); ><font size='4'> <strong>PARITALA SUDHAKAR<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF TELANGANA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 6 S.C.R. 180</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 655</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010001862025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SUDHANSHU DHULIA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The appellant was convicted for the offence punishable u/s.7 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 and also for the offence punishable u/s.13(1)(d) r/w. s.13(2) of the Act by the trial Court. The High Court affirmed the conviction of the appellant. Headnotes&dagger; &ndash; ss.7, 13(1)(d) r/w. s.13(2) &ndash; The complainant sought compensation for trees that dried due to drought &ndash; Allegation that appellant demanded a bribe of Rs.20,000/- to conduct an inquiry and prepare a report &ndash; A trap was laid for appellant &ndash; It was alleged that at<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 08-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 2541/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('2','2025','2025_6_180_192','2025INSC655','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><